    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
        android:text="          Sound is produced when the air in contact with the vibrating body is suddenly compressed.\n          Due to the elastic nature of the medium, these compressions are spread away from the source.\n          Hence, the vibrating body sets up waves of compressions and rarefactions in the air.\n          As these waves reach near our ear drums, we feel a sensation of hearing.\n
Audible waves : \n          Sound waves with frequency in the range of 20Hz to 20MHz.\n
Infrasonic waves :\n          Sound waves below audible range i.e. below 20Hz.\n
Ultrasonic waves :\n           Sound waves above audible range i.e. 20 kHz
"
        android:id="@+id/textView79"
        android:layout_alignTop="@+id/imageView23"
        android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
        android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
        android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
        android:textColor="#006699" />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
